<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7864292>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Genomic trees of Oarisma and an outgroup. The trees are constructed from protein-coding regions in a. nuclear genome, b. Z chromosome, and c. mitochondrial genome. Specimens are arranged in the same order in all trees and complete labels are given in panel a only. See Fig. 3 for other notations. Species discussed in the text are labeled in different colors: Oarisma (Oarisma) castanea (red), Oarisma (Copaeodes) jean (green), Oarisma (Copaeodes) favor, comb. nov. (magenta), and outgroups (Thymelicus) are gray. Statistical support values critical for the placement of O. castanea are highlighted in yellow." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7864292/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

